## When wiring password auth into an app

### Step 1 â€” Add module packs

**Backend:**

```typescript
import {ModulePackBE_PasswordAuth} from '@nu-art/password-auth-backend';
import {ApiDef_PasswordAuth} from '@nu-art/password-auth-shared';

// In Storm builder chain:
.addModulePack(ModulePackBE_PasswordAuth)

// In openApis array:
openApis: [ApiDef_PasswordAuth.login, ApiDef_PasswordAuth.registerAccount]
```

**Frontend:**

```typescript
import {ModulePackFE_PasswordAuth} from '@nu-art/password-auth-frontend';

// In Thunder builder chain:
.addModules(...ModulePackFE_PasswordAuth)
```

### Step 2 â€” Configure the backend

```typescript
ModuleBE_PasswordAuth: {
  canRegister: true,               // enable user self-registration
  passwordAssertion: {             // optional â€” password strength rules
    minLength: 8,
    requireUppercase: true,
    requireLowercase: true,
    requireDigit: true,
    requireSpecial: false,
  },
  ignorePasswordAssertion: false,  // set true to skip assertion (dev only)
}
```

When `canRegister` is `false`, the registration endpoint returns 418 (I'm a teapot).

### Step 3 â€” Add login/register UI

```typescript
import {Component_Login, Component_Register} from '@nu-art/password-auth-frontend';

// Login form (email + password):
<Component_Login />

// Registration form (email + password + password check):
<Component_Register />
```

For password change (requires authenticated session):

```typescript
import {Component_ChangePassword} from '@nu-art/password-auth-frontend';

<Component_ChangePassword />
```

